purrr とは

library(purrr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'purrr'
## 
##  以下のオブジェクトは 'package:dplyr' からマスクされています: 
## 
##      order_by 
## 
##  以下のオブジェクトは 'package:plyr' からマスクされています: 
## 
##      compact
purrr::map(c(1, 2, 3), ~ . + 1)
##  x = list 3 (216 bytes)
## .  [[1]] = double 1= 2
## .  [[2]] = double 1= 3
## .  [[3]] = double 1= 4
purrr::map(list(a = 1, b = 2, c = 3), ~ . + 1)
##  x = list 3 (544 bytes)
## .  a = double 1= 2
## .  b = double 1= 3
## .  c = double 1= 4
purrr::map2(c(1, 2, 3), c(4, 5, 6), ~ .x * .y)
##  x = list 3 (216 bytes)
## .  [[1]] = double 1= 4
## .  [[2]] = double 1= 10
## .  [[3]] = double 1= 18
purrr::map_int(list(a = 1L, b = 2L, c = 3L), ~ . + 1L)
## a b c 
## 2 3 4
purrr::keep(c(1, 2, 3), ~ . >= 2)
## [1] 2 3
purrr::keep(list(a = 1, b = 2, c = 3), ~ . >=  2)
##  x = list 2 (416 bytes)
## .  b = double 1= 2
## .  c = double 1= 3
purrr::reduce(c(1, 2, 3), `+`)
## [1] 6
purrr::reduce(list(a = 1, b = 2, c = 3), `+`)
## [1] 6
purrr::split_by(c(1, 2, 3), ~ . %% 2)
##  x = list 2 (424 bytes)
## .  0 = double 1= 2
## .  1 = double 2= 1 3
purrr::split_by(list(a = 1, b = 2, c = 3), ~ . %% 2)
##  x = list 2 (1040 bytes)
## .  0 = list 1
## . .  b = double 1= 2
## .  1 = list 2
## . .  a = double 1= 1
## . .  c = double 1= 3
purrr::sort_by(c(2, -3, 1), ~ abs(.))
## [1]  1  2 -3
purrr::order_by(c(2, -3, 1), ~ abs(.))
## [1] 3 1 2
purrr::sort_by(list(a = 2, b = - 3, c = 1), ~ abs(.))
##  x = list 3 (544 bytes)
## .  c = double 1= 1
## .  a = double 1= 2
## .  b = double 1= -3
purrr::order_by(list(a = 2, b = - 3, c = 1), ~ abs(.))
## [1] 3 1 2

data.frame への変換

set.seed(1)

ts1 <- ts(cumsum(runif(12, 0, 20)), start = 2000, freq = 12)

data.frame(time = time(ts1), values = ts1)
##        time     values
## 1  2000.000   5.310173
## 2  2000.083  12.752651
## 3  2000.167  24.209719
## 4  2000.250  42.373874
## 5  2000.333  46.407513
## 6  2000.417  64.375307
## 7  2000.500  83.268812
## 8  2000.583  96.484768
## 9  2000.667 109.067049
## 10 2000.750 110.302774
## 11 2000.833 114.422266
## 12 2000.917 117.953401
ts2 <- ts(cumsum(runif(12, 20, 30)), start = 2000, freq = 6)
ts3 <- ts(cumsum(runif(12, 20, 30)), start = 2000, freq = 3)
tss <- list(ts1=ts1, ts2=ts2, ts3=ts3)

tss %>%
  purrr::map(~ dplyr::data_frame(time = time(.), values = .)) %>%
  dplyr::bind_rows()
## Source: local data frame [36 x 2]
## 
##        time     values
##       (dbl)      (dbl)
## 1  2000.000   5.310173
## 2  2000.083  12.752651
## 3  2000.167  24.209719
## 4  2000.250  42.373874
## 5  2000.333  46.407513
## 6  2000.417  64.375307
## 7  2000.500  83.268812
## 8  2000.583  96.484768
## 9  2000.667 109.067049
## 10 2000.750 110.302774
## ..      ...        ...
res <- tss %>%
  purrr::map2(., names(.),
              ~ dplyr::data_frame(time = time(.x), values = .x, name = .y)) %>%
  dplyr::bind_rows()
ggplot(res, aes(time, values, colour = name)) + geom_line()

                           likes = sample(ndata, size = 2)))

set.seed(1)
gen <- function(name) {
  age = sample(30:35, size = 1)
  
  size = sample(1:(length(ndata) - 1), size = 1)
  likes = sample(ndata[ndata != name], size = size)
  
  return (list(name = name, age = age, likes = likes))
}
dummies <- map(ndata, ~ gen(.))

example 3: 複数のモデルの比較

df <- read.csv('data3a.csv')
head(df)
##    y     x f
## 1  6  8.31 C
## 2  6  9.44 C
## 3  6  9.50 C
## 4 12  9.07 C
## 5 10 10.16 C
## 6  4  8.32 C
# - y: 結実した種子数
# - x: サイズ
# - f: 施肥あり(T) / なし 
formulas <- list(mod1 = y ~ x, mod2 = y ~ f, mod3 = y ~ x + f) 
results <- purrr::map(formulas,
                      ~ glm(formula = ., family = poisson, data = df))

results[[1]]
## 
## Call:  glm(formula = ., family = poisson, data = df)
